{
  "texts": [
    "In § § 6.1-6.2, we treat the question of which classes of possibility frames are definable by modal formulas.",
    "Using the duality theory of § 5, we prove analogues for possibility semantics of Goldblatt's [1974] characterization of modally definable classes of world frames and Goldblatt and Thomason's [1975] characterization of modally definable classes of full world frames.",
    "In § 6.3, we discuss the question of which modal formulas define classes of possibility frames that are first-order definable.",
    "As noted by Goldblatt [2006a, p. 51], \"a substantial reason for the great success\" of Kripke semantics is the way in which many natural modal axioms correspond to first-order properties of the accessibility relations in Kripke frames, such as seriality (□φ → ♢φ), reflexivity (□φ → φ), transitivity (□φ → □□φ), symmetry (φ → □♢φ), and so on.",
    "Similarly, many natural modal axioms correspond to first-order properties of full possibility frames."
  ]
}